Claims CLAIMS What is claimed is: 1. A process for producing syngas and C 2 hydrocarbons comprising: (a) feeding an oxidative coupling of methane (OCM) reactant mixture to an OCM reaction zone; wherein the OCM reaction zone comprises an OCM catalyst; wherein the OCM reactant mixture comprises methane (CH 4 ), oxygen (O 2 ), and optionally carbon dioxide (CO 2 ); wherein at least a portion of the OCM reactant mixture reacts in the OCM reaction zone to produce an OCM product mixture; wherein a portion of the methane in the OCM reactant mixture reacts, via an OCM reaction, to produce C 2 hydrocarbons; and wherein the OCM product mixture comprises C 2 hydrocarbons, carbon dioxide, hydrogen (H 2 ), carbon monoxide (CO), water, and methane; (b) feeding a catalytic partial oxidation (CPO) reactant mixture to a CPO reaction zone; wherein the CPO reaction zone comprises a CPO catalyst; wherein the CPO reactant mixture comprises at least a portion of the OCM product mixture, supplemental oxygen, and optionally supplemental carbon dioxide; wherein at least a portion of the CPO reactant mixture reacts in the CPO reaction zone to produce a CPO reaction zone product mixture; wherein a first portion of the methane in the CPO reactant mixture reacts, via a CPO reaction, to produce H 2 and CO; wherein a second portion of the methane in the CPO reactant mixture optionally reacts, via a dry reforming reaction, to produce H 2 and CO; wherein the CPO reaction zone product mixture comprises H 2 , CO, C 2 hydrocarbons, carbon dioxide, water, and methane; wherein the amount of methane in the CPO reaction zone product mixture is less than the amount of methane in the OCM product mixture; and wherein the amount of hydrogen in the CPO reaction zone product mixture is greater than the amount of hydrogen in the OCM product mixture; and (c) recovering a C 2 hydrocarbons stream and a syngas stream from the CPO reaction zone product mixture, wherein the syngas stream comprises H 2 and CO. 2. The process of claim 1, wherein (i) a common reactor comprises both the OCM reaction zone and the CPO reaction zone, or (ii) a first reactor comprises the OCM reaction zone a second reactor comprises the CPO reaction zone. 3. The process of claim 1, wherein the syngas stream comprises methane in an amount of from about 0.1 mol% to about 6 mol%. 4. The process of claim 1, wherein the syngas stream is characterized by a H 2 /CO molar ratio of from about 1.9 to about 2.2. 5. The process of claim 1 further comprising recovering a water stream and a carbon dioxide stream from the CPO reaction zone product mixture, wherein at least a portion of the carbon dioxide stream is fed to the OCM reaction zone in step (a) and/or to the CPO reaction zone in step (b). 6. The process of claim 1 further comprising heating the OCM reactant mixture to a temperature of equal to or greater than about 400 oC prior to introducing to the OCM reaction zone in step (a). 7. The process of claim 1, wherein the OCM reactant mixture is characterized by a methane to oxygen molar ratio of from about 4:1 to about 16:1, and wherein the CPO reactant mixture comprises oxygen in an amount of from about 10 mol% to about 30 mol%. 8. The process of claim 1, wherein the OCM catalyst comprises one or more metal oxides; wherein the one or more metal oxides is selected from the group consisting of MgO, La 2 O 3 , Sm 2 O 3 , CaO, Ce 2 O 3 , Sr a Ce b Yb c O x , and combinations thereof; wherein a is 1.0; wherein b is from about 0.1 to about 3.0; wherein c is from about 0.01 to about 1.0; and wherein x balances the oxidation states. 9. The process of claim 1, wherein the CPO catalyst comprises one or more metals; wherein the one or more metals is selected from the group consisting of Ni, Fe, Co, Re, Ir, Rh, Ru, Pd, Pt, and combinations thereof; wherein the CPO catalyst further comprises a metal oxide support; wherein at least a portion of the one or more metals contacts, coats, is embedded in, is supported by, and/or is distributed throughout at least a portion of the metal oxide support; and wherein the metal oxide support is selected from the group consisting of Al 2 O 3 , TiO 2 , La 2 O 3 , Sm 2 O 3 , Ce 2 O 3 , MgO, CaO, and combinations thereof. 10. The process of claim 1, wherein OCM reaction zone is operated at a temperature ranging from about 800 oC to about 1,100 oC and at a pressure ranging from about 5 barg to about 11 barg. 11. The process of claim 1, wherein the CPO reaction zone is operated at a temperature ranging from about 600 oC to about 1,000 oC and at a pressure ranging from about 2 barg to about 10 barg. 12. The process of claim 1, wherein the overall methane conversion is from about 80% to about 99%, based on the moles of methane fed to the OCM reaction zone. 13. The process of claim 1, wherein the overall productivity rate is from about 1.3 tons to about 1.9 tons of C 2 hydrocarbons and syngas produced per ton of CH 4 fed to the OCM reaction zone. 14. The process of claim 1, wherein the overall C 2 hydrocarbons yield is from about 15% to about 20%, based on the moles of methane fed to the OCM reaction zone. 15. A process for producing syngas and C 2 hydrocarbons comprising feeding a reactant mixture to an oxidative conversion reactor; wherein the reactant mixture comprises methane, oxygen, and optionally carbon dioxide; wherein at least a portion of the reactant mixture reacts in the oxidative conversion reactor to produce an oxidative conversion product mixture; wherein the oxidative conversion reactor comprises an oxidative conversion catalyst system; wherein the oxidative conversion catalyst system comprises an oxidative coupling of methane (OCM) catalyst component and a catalytic partial oxidation (CPO) catalyst component; wherein a first portion of the methane reacts in the presence of the OCM catalyst component, via an OCM reaction, to produce C 2 hydrocarbons; wherein a second portion of the methane reacts in the presence of the CPO catalyst component, via a CPO reaction, to produce hydrogen (H 2 ) and carbon monoxide (CO); wherein the OCM catalyst component comprises one or more metal oxides selected from the group consisting of MgO, La 2 O 3 , Sm 2 O 3 , CaO, Ce 2 O 3 , Sr 1 Ce 0.9 Yb 0.1 O 3 , and combinations thereof; 

 wherein the CPO catalyst component comprises one or more metals selected from the group consisting of Ni, Fe, Co, Re, Ir, Rh, Ru, Pd, Pt, and combinations thereof; wherein the oxidative conversion catalyst system further comprises a metal oxide support; wherein at least a portion of the OCM catalyst component and/or at least a portion of the CPO catalyst component contact, coat, are embedded in, are supported by, and/or are distributed throughout at least a portion of the metal oxide support; wherein the metal oxide support is selected from the group consisting of Al 2 O 3 , TiO 2 , La 2 O 3 , Sm 2 O 3 , Ce 2 O 3 , MgO, CaO, and combinations thereof; wherein the OCM catalyst component and the metal oxide support are the same or different; and wherein the oxidative conversion product mixture comprises C 2 hydrocarbons, syngas, carbon dioxide, water, and methane; and wherein the syngas comprises H 2 and CO. 16. The process of claim 15 further comprising recovering a C 2 hydrocarbons stream, a syngas stream, a carbon dioxide stream, and a water stream from the oxidative conversion product mixture; wherein the C 2 hydrocarbons stream comprises ethylene and ethane; wherein the syngas stream comprises methane in an amount of from about 0.1 mol% to about 6 mol%; wherein the syngas stream is characterized by a H 2 /CO molar ratio of from about 1.9 to about 2.2; and wherein at least a portion of the carbon dioxide stream is optionally recycled to the oxidative conversion reactor. 17. The process of claim 15, wherein (A) the oxidative conversion reactor comprises (i) a single reaction zone, wherein the single reaction zone comprises both the OCM catalyst component and the CPO catalyst component; or (ii) an OCM reaction zone comprising the OCM catalyst component and a CPO reaction zone comprising the CPO catalyst component, wherein the CPO reaction zone is downstream of the OCM reaction zone; or (B) the first portion of the methane reacts in the presence of the OCM catalyst component, via an OCM reaction, to produce C 2 hydrocarbons simultaneously with the second portion of the methane reacting in the presence of the CPO catalyst component, via a CPO reaction, to produce hydrogen (H 2 ) and carbon monoxide (CO). 18. The process of claim 15 further comprising staged oxygen addition along a length of the oxidative conversion reactor. 19. The process of claim 15, wherein the overall methane conversion is from about 80% to about 99%, based on the moles of methane fed to the oxidative conversion reactor; wherein the overall productivity rate is from about 1.3 tons to about 1.9 tons of C 2 hydrocarbons and syngas produced per ton of methane fed to the oxidative conversion reactor; and wherein the overall C 2 hydrocarbons yield is from about 15% to about 20%, based on the moles of methane fed to the oxidative conversion reactor. 20. A process for producing syngas and C 2 hydrocarbons comprising: (a) heating an oxidative coupling of methane (OCM) reactant mixture in a preheating zone to a temperature of equal to or greater than about 400 oC to yield a preheated OCM reactant mixture; wherein the preheated OCM reactant mixture comprises methane, oxygen, and carbon dioxide; and wherein the preheated OCM reactant mixture is characterized by a methane to oxygen molar ratio of from about 4:1 to about 16:1; 

 (b) feeding at least a portion of the preheated OCM reactant mixture to an OCM reaction zone; wherein the OCM reaction zone comprises an OCM catalyst; wherein the OCM catalyst comprises one or more metal oxides; wherein at least a portion of the preheated OCM reactant mixture reacts in the OCM reaction zone to produce an OCM product mixture; wherein a portion of the methane in the preheated OCM reactant mixture reacts, via an OCM reaction, to produce C 2 hydrocarbons; wherein OCM reaction zone is operated at a temperature ranging from about 800 oC to about 1,100 oC and at a pressure ranging from about 5 barg to about 11 barg; and wherein the OCM product mixture comprises C 2 hydrocarbons, carbon dioxide, hydrogen (H 2 ), carbon monoxide (CO), water, and methane; (c) feeding a catalytic partial oxidation (CPO) reactant mixture to a CPO reaction zone; wherein the CPO reaction zone comprises a CPO catalyst; wherein the CPO catalyst comprises one or more metals; wherein the CPO reactant mixture comprises at least a portion of the OCM product mixture and supplemental oxygen; wherein the CPO reactant mixture comprises oxygen in an amount of from about 10 mol% to about 30 mol%; wherein at least a portion of the CPO reactant mixture reacts in the CPO reaction zone to produce a CPO reaction zone product mixture; wherein a first portion of the methane in the CPO reactant mixture reacts, via a CPO reaction, to produce H 2 and CO; wherein a second portion of the methane in the CPO reactant mixture reacts, via a dry reforming reaction, to produce H 2 and CO; wherein the CPO reaction zone is operated at a temperature ranging from about 600 oC to about 1,000 oC and at a pressure ranging from about 2 barg to about 10 barg; wherein the CPO reaction zone product mixture comprises H 2 , CO, C 2 hydrocarbons, carbon dioxide, water, and methane; wherein the amount of methane in the CPO reaction zone product mixture is less than the amount of methane in the OCM product mixture; and wherein the amount of hydrogen in the CPO reaction zone product mixture is greater than the amount of hydrogen in the OCM product mixture; (d) recovering a C 2 hydrocarbons stream, a syngas stream, a carbon dioxide stream, and a water stream from the CPO reaction zone product mixture; wherein the C 2 hydrocarbons stream comprises ethylene and ethane; wherein the syngas stream comprises methane in an amount of from about 0.1 mol% to about 5 mol%; and wherein the syngas stream is characterized by a H 2 /CO molar ratio of from about 1.9 to about 2.2; and (e) recycling at least a portion of the carbon dioxide stream to the preheating zone in step (a), the OCM reaction zone in step (b), the CPO reaction zone in step (c), or combinations thereof, wherein the OCM catalyst comprises one or more metal oxides selected from the group consisting of MgO, La 2 O 3 , Sm 2 O 3 , CaO, Ce 2 O 3 , Sr a Ce b Yb c O x , and combinations thereof; wherein a is 1.0; wherein b is from about 0.1 to about 3.0; wherein c is from about 0.01 to about 1.0; and wherein x balances the oxidation states and wherein the CPO catalyst comprises one or more metals selected from the group consisting of Ni, Fe, Co, Re, Ir, Rh, Ru, Pd, Pt, and combinations thereof; wherein the CPO catalyst further comprises a metal oxide support; wherein at least a portion of the one or more metals contacts, coats, is embedded in, is supported by, and/or is distributed throughout at least a portion of the metal oxide support; and wherein the metal oxide support is selected from the group consisting of Al 2 O 3 , TiO 2 , La 2 O 3 , Sm 2 O 3 , Ce 2 O 3 , MgO, CaO, and combinations thereof.
